      "content": "For an established and controlled look, tidy, conservative hairstyles are best for most executive males. This often means a clean, well-maintained cut—perhaps a classic taper or side-part—that stays perfectly in place without excessive product. For females, sleek, polished looks like a low bun, a sharp bob, or perfectly styled, controlled waves convey gravitas. The general rule is polished precision; anything overly trendy or messy detracts from perceived authority.",
